<h2 id="laion-5b">LAION-5B</h2>
<p><em>The largest open-source image-text dataset</em> 
<a href="https://proceedings.neurips.cc/paper_files/paper/2022/file/a1859debfb3b59d094f3504d5ebb6c25-Paper-Datasets_and_Benchmarks.pdf">Paper</a></p>

<p><strong>Outstanding Paper @ NeurIPS 2022</strong></p>

<p>Built infrastructure to process, embed, and benchmark retrieval over the LAION-5B dataset using CLIP. Designed pipelines for preprocessing, chunked embedding generation, and nearest neighbor retrieval using FAISS. Focused on scalable indexing and hybrid search evaluation across multilingual and multimodal document sets.</p>

<h2 id="lantern-rd-raw">LANTERN-RD-RAW</h2>
<p><em>Comprehensive Dataset of Invasive Spotted Lanternfly Imagery</em><br />
<a href="https://github.com/srkvatsa/LANTERN-RD-RAW">GitHub Repository</a></p>

<p>Developed LANTERN-RD, an extensive dataset focusing on the invasive spotted lanternfly (SLF). This work was presented at CVPR and NeurIPS workshops and has been inducted into the Harvard-NASA ADS. The dataset aims to aid in the mitigation of SLF through deep learning applications.</p>

